word_mean_info__list.difference: 侧重出发地而不是目的地。
可与leave换用，强调目的地，但不及leave普通。
较正式用词，指经过周密考虑或郑重地离开，强调离开的起点。
侧重指离开令人烦恼的地方，或摆脱使人不快的人或事。
一般用词，指从所在地到其它地方去，着重目的地而非出发地。
侧重指变得与原来截然不同，有时含贬义。
常指某人或某物有意无意地获得引起变化的因素，结果使变成另一状态。
常指逐渐地变成新状态，强调渐变的过程。
最普通用词，作为连系动词，指从一个状态向另一个状态的变化。
侧重变化的经过或过程，多用于不良情况。
作为连系动词，通常与形容词连用，指进入某种状态，从而发生变化，多指不好的状态。
指按某一既定目标前进，取得发展，目的性很明确，强调经常和稳定地前进。
非正式用语，侧重从某一停止点向某地前进，但不表示前进的目的地。
主要用于具体的人或物，也可指科学技术和运动等。
最常用词，含义宽泛而不确切，依上文确定其具体意思。

With all my strength I shouted, "Go, Black Star, go!"

bilingual.source: Shall we go and see the museum?

list.abstract: Go（英 [ɡəʊ]，美 [ɡoʊ]），英语单词。作动词为去；启程；想要等。作名词为试验；精神；生气等。作形容词为运行正常的。例句：And it makes them strongly believe that they would go beyond the mountains one day.（这使他们坚信，有一天他们会在另一边的山脉）。 Go的近义词有walk，step，track等。反义词有stay in place，come，malfunction等。
Go是开发Android应用的一种BASIC语言，发布于2009年。

yingyinNormal.zh: 你说吧。你要迟到了！快去。

yingyinNormal.en: I'll go see how he's doing. No. I will.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我去看看他怎么样。不，我去。
那我就直接不穿胸罩去了。

yingyinNormal.en: Just go. I'll catch up with you. All right.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们先去吧，我等下就去找你们。好吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Come on. Go. Now. That's why I'm clapping.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好了！去吧。拍手的意思就是要大家去做事。

yingyinNormal.en: I have to go to bond court.
Let's go watch it at your place.

yingyinNormal.zh: 你去的是哪家麻省理工来着？

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

word_level_phrase_info.phrase: have a long way to go

sense_info_list.en: move from one place or point to another

examination_example.sentence: People who do so probaly live so cautiously that they <highlight>go</highlight> nowhere.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这样做的人可能生活得非常谨慎，以至于他们哪儿也去不了。

examination_example.sentence: It requires minimal effort and <highlight>goes</highlight> a long way.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它只需要很少的努力，而且会走很长的路。

examination_example.sentence: Even dairy farms, where robots do a small share of milking, have a long way to <highlight>go</highlight> before they're automated.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 即使是机器人只负责一小部分挤奶的奶牛场，在自动化之前也还有很长的路要走。

examination_example.sentence: If you think other people are <highlight>going</highlight> to disagree, too, you might want to gather your army first.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你认为其他人也会不同意，你可能想先集结你的军队。

examination_example.sentence: They are our happy glasses that protect us from what we perceive is <highlight>going</highlight> to be more dangerous.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它们是我们快乐的眼镜，保护我们免受我们认为会变得更加危险的事情的影响。

examination_example.sentence: Suppose you are <highlight>going</highlight> to study abroad and share an apartment with John, a local student.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 假设你要出国留学，和当地的学生约翰合租一套公寓。

sense_info_list.zh: 变成; 进入(某种状态)

examination_example.sentence: It could <highlight>go</highlight> into effect within the next few weeks.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它（措施）可能在未来几周内生效。

examination_example.sentence: Professionals trying to acquire new skills will be able to do so without <highlight>going</highlight> into debt.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 试图获得新技能的专业人士将能够做到这一点，而不会负债。

examination_example.sentence: After bills, Tony has £60 a week to spend, £40 of which <highlight>goes</highlight> on food.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 除了账单，托尼一周有60英镑可花，其中40英镑用于购买食品。

sense_info_list.zh: 运行; 发展; 进展

examination_example.sentence: So they feel a responsibility to you to keep that relationship <highlight>going</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 所以他们觉得你有责任维持这段关系。

examination_example.sentence: Among the annoying challenges facing the middle class is one that will probably <highlight>go</highlight> unmentioned in the next presidential campaign.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 中产阶级面临的令人讨厌的挑战中，有一个可能在下一届总统竞选中不会被提及。

examination_example.sentence: "The human systems and the landscapes we live on are linked, and the interactions <highlight>go</highlight> both ways," he says.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人类系统和我们赖以生存的景观是相互联系的，相互作用是双向的。

examination_example.sentence: It's almost impossible to <highlight>go</highlight> through life without experiencing some kind of failure.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 经历人生而不经历某种失败几乎是不可能的。

examination_example.sentence: We are <highlight>going</highlight> through life facing sad experiences.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们正在经历面对悲伤过往的生活。

examination_example.sentence: Sometimes it is easy to feel bad because you are <highlight>going</highlight> through tough times.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有时候很容易感觉不好，因为你正在经历艰难的时期。

examination_example.sentence: Yet science has a cultural history, too, with roots <highlight>going</highlight> back to the dawn of civilization.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，科学也有文化历史，其根源可以追溯到文明的开端。

examination_example.sentence: Justice Antonin Scalia offered an even more robust defense of state privileges <highlight>going</highlight> back to the Alien and Sedition Acts.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Antonin Scalia大法官，他为可追溯到《外国人法和煽动叛乱法》的州特权提供了更加强有力的辩护。

examination_example.sentence: Some of their ties <highlight>go</highlight> back a long way.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们的一些关系可以追溯到很久以前。

examination_example.sentence: It may <highlight>go</highlight> against the Constitution.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这可能违反宪法。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Go</highlight> against human nature.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 违背人性。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Go</highlight> against state laws.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 违反州法律。

sense_info_list.en: have a specified content or wording

examination_example.sentence: A move back to self-sufficiency, the argument <highlight>goes</highlight>, would boost the farming industry, political sovereignty and even the nation's health.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这种观点认为，回归自给自足将促进农业、政治主权甚至国家健康。

examination_example.sentence: Why, the argument <highlight>goes</highlight>, should a car-driving pensioner from Lincolnshire have to subsidise the daily commute of a stockbroker from Surrey?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这种观点认为，为什么林肯郡的一名汽车驾驶养老金领取者必须补贴萨里郡股票经纪人的日常通勤？

examination_example.sentence: You cannot buy class, as the old saying <highlight>goes</highlight>, and these upstart entrepreneurs cannot buy their prizes the prestige of the Nobels.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 正如古语有云：你不能购买等级。这些自命不凡的企业家也不能为他们的奖项购买诺贝尔奖的名望。

examination_example.sentence: That means more battles like the one now <highlight>going</highlight> on between the Justice Department and California.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这意味着更多的战斗，就像现在司法部和加州之间正在进行的那样。

examination_example.sentence: What is <highlight>going</highlight> on?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 发生什么事了？

examination_example.sentence: One of the astonishing revelations was how little Rebekah Brooks knew of what <highlight>went</highlight> on in her newsroom.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 其中令人震惊的一个发现，就是Rebekah Brooks竟然对她的新闻编辑部里所发生的事情几乎一无所知。

examination_example.sentence: Exploring the contents of a smartphone is similar to <highlight>going</highlight> through a suspect's purse.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 翻看智能手机的内容相当于翻查嫌疑犯的钱包。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Going</highlight> through one's wallet.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 翻钱包。

examination_example.sentence: Police don't violate the Fourth Amendment when they <highlight>go</highlight> through the wallet or pocketbook of an arrestee without a warrant.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 警察在没有搜查令的情况下搜查被捕者的钱包或钱夹，并不违反第四修正案。

examination_example.sentence: The move to renewables now account for more than half of new power sources <highlight>going</highlight> on line.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 向可再生能源转型现在约占正在使用的新能源的一半多。

examination_example.sentence: Another nationwide concern is whether public funds from other agencies are <highlight>going</highlight> into construction in fire-prone districts.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 另一个全国性的担忧是，其他机构的公共资金是否会投入到火灾多发区的建设中。

examination_example.sentence: In effect, fewer federal funds today are <highlight>going</highlight> towards the agency's other work that affect the lives of all Americans.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 实际上，如今联邦资金很少投入其他一些与全体美国人息息相关的工作上。

examination_example.sentence: And if real, she notes, it might be reversible by another nudge: "Easy come, easy <highlight>go</highlight>."
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她指出，如果是真的，它可能会被另一次轻推逆转：“来得轻松，去得也快。”

examination_example.sentence: The very pressing need for more affordable housing is real and is not <highlight>going</highlight> away.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对更多经济适用房的迫切需求是真实的，并且不会消失。

examination_example.sentence: Certain jobs have <highlight>gone</highlight> away for good, outmoded by machines.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 某些工作已经永远消失了，被机器淘汰了。

examination_example.sentence: Time is finite, the older you get, the quicker it seems to <highlight>go</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 时间是有限的，你年龄越大，时间似乎流逝得越快。

examination_example.sentence: Long <highlight>gone</highlight> are the days when a boss could simply give an employee contractual notice.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 老板可以简单地向员工发出合同通知书的日子已经一去不复返了。

examination_example.sentence: They found that middle-aged people with higher measures of abdominal fat scored worse on measures of fluid intelligence as the years <highlight>went</highlight> by.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们发现，随着时间的推移，腹部脂肪含量较高的中年人在流体智力方面得分更低。

examination_example.sentence: The reach of art-science tie-ups needs to <highlight>go</highlight> beyond the necessary purpose of research communication, and participants.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 艺术与科学的合作需要超越研究交流的必要目的，甚至是参与者本身。

examination_example.sentence: The ban on ultra-thin models seems to <highlight>go</highlight> beyond protecting models from starving themselves to death.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对超薄机型的禁令似乎不仅仅是保护机型不消失。

examination_example.sentence: It is true that CEO pay has <highlight>gone</highlight> up.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 首席执行官的工资确实上涨了。

examination_example.sentence: One reason their pay has <highlight>gone</highlight> up so much is that CEOs really have upped their game relative.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们的工资上涨如此之多的一个原因是，首席执行官们确实提高了他们的事务水平。

examination_example.sentence: Don't <highlight>go</highlight> it alone.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 不要单干。

examination_example.sentence: Also unclear is why Microsoft has <highlight>gone</highlight> it alone.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 同样不清楚的是，微软为何单干。

examination_example.sentence: The G.I. was the common man grown into hero who <highlight>went</highlight> without the necessities of food and shelter.
examination_example.sentence_trans: G.I.是一个食不果腹、居无定所，成为英雄的普通人。

examination_example.sentence: Then, too, the company <highlight>went</highlight> along.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然后，公司也赞同了。

examination_example.sentence: The Times shouldn't waste time getting out of the print business, but only if they <highlight>go</highlight> about doing it the right way.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 《泰晤士报》不应该浪费时间退出印刷行业，但前提是他们要以正确的方式处理。

examination_example.sentence: Indeed, the Flatiron students might not <highlight>go</highlight> into IT at all.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实上，弗拉铁的学生可能根本不会从事信息技术领域。

examination_example.sentence: If you have surplus vegetables, you'll do a vegetable soup, and all fruits threatening to "<highlight>go</highlight> off" will be cooked or juiced.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你有多余的蔬菜，你会做一个蔬菜汤，所有恐怕会“变质”的水果都会被煮熟或榨汁。

examination_example.sentence: Its reputation in Vermont is already so damaged that it has nothing left to lose by <highlight>going</highlight> to war with the state.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它（公司）在佛蒙特已经声名狼藉了，就算和州政府再打一场官司也不会有更大损失。

examination_example.sentence: Facebook broke the promise almost as soon as the deal <highlight>went</highlight> through.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 交易一批准，Facebook就违背了诺言。

examination_example.sentence: Pick a standard work uniform or a few <highlight>go</highlight>-to options.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 选择一套标准的工作服或一些征询意见的选择。

examination_example.sentence: AT&T decided to do a massive reskilling program rather than <highlight>go</highlight> with a fire-and-hire strategy.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国电话电报公司决定做一个大规模的再培训项目，而不赞成解雇和雇佣的策略。

examination_example.sentence: For individual companies, the temptation is always to let <highlight>go</highlight> of workers whose skills are no longer in demand.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对于个别公司来说，他们喜欢的做法总是抛弃那些技能不再有用的员工。

examination_example.sentence: The "mommy wars" of the 1990s are still <highlight>going</highlight> on today.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 二十世纪九十年代的"妈咪大战'如今仍在继续。

examination_example.sentence: James Herriot did not find it easy in his early days of, as he put it,"having a <highlight>go</highlight> at the writing game".
examination_example.sentence_trans: 正如James Herriot所言，他早年在“写作游戏中的尝试” 并不容易。

examination_example.sentence: A weather expert invited him to <highlight>go</highlight> there for his mission.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一位气象专家邀请他去那里执行任务。

examination_example.sentence: Perhaps it'll be better getting things off my chest by <highlight>going</highlight> to one of those rate-your-employer websites.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 也许去那些给你的雇主打分的网站把我的心事一吐为快会更好。

examination_example.sentence: Why did the woman and those who <highlight>went</highlight> with her end their trip halfway?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为什么这个女人和那些和她一起去的人中途结束了他们的旅行？

examination_example.sentence: Avoid <highlight>going</highlight> over the same options repeatedly.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 避免重复讨论相同的选项。

examination_example.sentence: Optimizing isn't the problem, but rather the process that we <highlight>go</highlight> through.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 优化不是问题，而是我们经历的过程。

examination_example.sentence: The most toxic part of decision making is <highlight>going</highlight> over the same options time and time again.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 决策过程中危害最大的部分就是一次又一次地重复同样的选择。

sense_info_list.zh: 变成; 变为; 变得

examination_example.sentence: They find their voice <highlight>go</highlight> unheeded.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们发现自己的声音无人理睬。

examination_example.sentence: By <highlight>going</highlight> into financial lockdown, Nicole gained financial independence.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 进入财务封锁期后，妮可获得了财务独立。

examination_example.sentence: Once again people began to argue whether Notre Dame Cathedral was <highlight>going</highlight> to collapse even without the fire.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人们再次开始争论，即使没有火灾，巴黎圣母院是否会倒塌。

examination_example.sentence: As the saying <highlight>goes</highlight>, it is better not to believe in books at all, rather than to believe in them implicitly.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 俗话说，与其对书半信半疑，不如完全不相信书。

examination_example.sentence: As the saying <highlight>goes</highlight>, too much water drowned the miller.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 常言道，过犹不及。

examination_example.sentence: Most of that money needs to <highlight>go</highlight> towards improving agricultural infrastructure.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大部分资金需要用于改善农业基础设施。

examination_example.sentence: So it is advisable for our parents to let <highlight>go</highlight> and launch children on the journey to independence.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 所以我们的父母应该放手让孩子踏上独立的旅程。

examination_example.sentence: There have been so many viruses <highlight>going</highlight> around this winter.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 今年冬天已经有很多病毒在传播了。

examination_example.sentence: What does Sarah say she is <highlight>going</highlight> to do?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 莎拉说她打算做什么？

examination_example.sentence: But the marketing strategy in response to this consumer demand has <highlight>gone</highlight> beyond articulating what is in a product.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是响应这种消费者需求的营销策略已经超越了阐明产品的内容。

examination_example.sentence: They foresee this being something that could give their estates and give their families the ability to make money from their likeness when they're <highlight>gone</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: “他们预见到这是能让他们的遗产让他们的家人在他们离开后有能力从他们的肖像中赚钱的东西。”

examination_example.sentence: You have to let <highlight>go</highlight> of your faith if you want to be a scientist.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你想成为一名科学家，你必须放弃你的信仰。

sense_info_list.zh: (go a long way towards doing)(对做某事)帮助很大

examination_example.sentence: And acknowledging this in an interview will <highlight>go</highlight> a long way towards suggesting that you might be the right person for the position.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在面试中承认这一点将大大有助于暗示你可能是这个职位的合适人选。

examination_example.sentence: And your chances of being more carefully considered for the job can quickly <highlight>go</highlight> down hill.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你被更仔细地考虑这份工作的机会可能会很快下降。

examination_example.sentence: Let's <highlight>go</highlight> back to my house and we can call the repair shop, and you can have some tea and cookies too.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 回我家吧，我们可以给修理店打电话，你也可以喝点茶，吃点饼干。

examination_example.sentence: Also, if you're interested in wine, you could <highlight>go</highlight> on a tour of the places where they grow grapes and make wine.

examination_example.sentence: Alternatively, they would <highlight>go</highlight> to the other extreme, and micro-analyze everything, to the point of complete inaction.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 或者，他们会走向另一个极端，微观分析一切，直到彻底不作为的地步。

examination_example.sentence: About 75% of elderly parents who don't <highlight>go</highlight> to nursing homes live within 30 minutes of at least one of their children.

examination_example.sentence: Probably their math anxiety will <highlight>go</highlight> unnoticed because their performance is good.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 可能他们的数学焦虑会被忽视，因为他们的表现很好。

examination_example.sentence: Right, you've convinced me. I'm going to <highlight>go</highlight> on the computer now and give it a try.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 好的，你说服我了。我现在要打开电脑试一试。

examination_example.sentence: While some of the budget airlines might use brighter, bolder shades, most others <highlight>go</highlight> with softened tones.

examination_example.sentence: Right, you've convinced me. I'm <highlight>going</highlight> to go on the computer now and give it a try.

examination_example.sentence: If we're not careful about all these minor problems right now, the effect on the future generation is <highlight>going</highlight> to be much bigger.

examination_example.sentence: You're not <highlight>going</highlight> to quit, are you?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你不会辞职吧？

examination_example.sentence: There's a huge amount of time and effort that <highlight>goes</highlight> into the process of selecting who gets grants.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在选择谁获得资助的过程中需要投入大量的时间和精力。

examination_example.sentence: It still has to <highlight>go</highlight> into a container.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它还是要放进一个容器里。

examination_example.sentence: The big food companies-which want to sell anything except the raw ingredients that <highlight>go</highlight> into cooking-made the home cook an endangered species.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大型食品公司希望出售除烹饪原料以外的任何东西，这使得家庭烹饪成为一种濒危物种。

examination_example.sentence: I am logged in, and I'll give that a <highlight>go</highlight>.

examination_example.sentence: Their weight will <highlight>go</highlight> down.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们的体重会下降。

examination_example.sentence: A fourth of this year's U. S. grain harvest will <highlight>go</highlight> to fuel cars.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 今年美国粮食收成的四分之一将用于燃料汽车。

examination_example.sentence: Surprisingly, the Space Roaster concept—should it <highlight>go</highlight> ahead—will not be the first attempt to take coffee into space.

examination_example.sentence: There's a whole lot <highlight>going</highlight> on.

examination_example.sentence: As the song <highlight>goes</highlight>, this long and winding road "will never disappear", and it will always stick in the visitor's memory.

examination_example.sentence: When the sun <highlight>goes</highlight> down, the stars (星星) come out.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当太阳落山时，星星就会出来。

examination_example.sentence: Over the past ten years, the price of solar panels has <highlight>gone</highlight> down greatly.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 过去十年，太阳能电池板的价格大幅下降。

examination_example.sentence: The waitress quickly went to get change, but the old lady was <highlight>gone</highlight> when the waitress came back．
examination_example.sentence_trans: 女服务员赶紧去拿零钱，但当她回来的时候，老太太已经走了。

examination_example.sentence: Gardening is a great way to get exercise without worrying about whether you're any good at it, or whether you're <highlight>going</highlight> to win.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 园艺是一种很好的锻炼方式，无需担心自己是否擅长或能否获胜。

examination_example.sentence: I'm <highlight>going</highlight> to choose some online courses with a friend of mine to improve our English.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我打算和我的一个朋友一起选择一些在线课程，来提高我们的英语水平。

examination_example.sentence: We are <highlight>going</highlight> to take a plane to Beijing.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们要坐飞机去北京。

examination_example.sentence: He has <highlight>gone</highlight> blind.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他已经失明了。

examination_example.sentence: Or we might say, "There is a tiny problem," when something has <highlight>gone</highlight> totally wrong.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 或者当事情完全出错的时候，我们可能会说：“有一个小问题”。

examination_example.sentence: When our lungs have <highlight>gone</highlight> bad, we realize that we need to stop smoking.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当我们的肺变差时，我们意识到我们需要戒烟了。

examination_example.sentence: Now she has <highlight>gone</highlight> through the dark times.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 现在，她已经度过了黑暗时期。

examination_example.sentence: Over the next month, I <highlight>went</highlight> through a lot of changes.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在接下来的一个月里，我经历了很多变化。

examination_example.sentence: Only being strong and optimistic, can one <highlight>go</highlight> through difficulties.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 只有坚强乐观，才能渡过难关。

examination_example.sentence: As the old saying <highlight>goes</highlight>, "A picture can say a thousand words. "
examination_example.sentence_trans: 古语有云：“一画胜千言。”

examination_example.sentence: As the saying <highlight>goes</highlight>, smiling is sunshine in everyone's heart.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 常言道，微笑是每个人心中的阳光。

examination_example.sentence_trans: 实验中使用的材料很容易找到，以便班主任可以在公共汽车开走后和全班学生一起重复实验。

examination_example.sentence: The organization wants the farmers to <highlight>go</highlight> on working together, helping each other and learning from each other.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 该组织希望农民继续合作，互相帮助，互相学习。

examination_example.sentence: To get permission for college, she <highlight>went</highlight> on three-day-hunger strike (抗议).
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为了能被准许去上大学，她进行了为期三天的绝食抗议。

examination_example.sentence: She was <highlight>going</highlight> over our writing.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她在检查我们的文章。

examination_example.sentence: She always knows what's <highlight>going</highlight> on in class, even when her students are passing notes behind her back.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她总是知道课堂上发生了什么，甚至当她的学生在她背后传递笔记的时候。

examination_example.sentence: How is everything <highlight>going</highlight> with you?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你的一切进展如何？

examination_example.sentence: Will was trying to find a good food choice to take the place of the bread, but it wasn't <highlight>going</highlight> very well.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 威尔试图找到一个好的食物来代替面包，但进展并不顺利。

examination_example.sentence: Tony's sister enjoys listening to music and she often <highlight>goes</highlight> to concerts.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 托尼的姐姐喜欢听音乐，她经常去听音乐会。

examination_example.sentence: Children <highlight>go</highlight> to school with batteries.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 孩子们带着电池上学。

examination_example.sentence: Dale once gave up the chance to <highlight>go</highlight> to college.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 戴尔曾经放弃了上大学的机会。

examination_example.sentence: In one experiment, the user asked Pepper to lay the napkin at the wrong place, <highlight>going</highlight> against the rules.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在某一个实验中，用户让派伯把餐巾放置在错误的地方，这违反了规则。

examination_example.sentence: The same <highlight>goes</highlight> for Laura.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这同样适用于劳拉。

examination_example.sentence: We all know that my students often <highlight>go</highlight> online, but we were surprised that ninety percent of them use the Internet every day.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们都知道我的学生经常上网，但我们惊讶于他们当中的百分之九十每天都使用互联网。

examination_example.sentence: Remember, your goals can be changed as time <highlight>goes</highlight> on.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 请记住，随着时间的推移，您的目标可能会发生变化。

examination_example.sentence: It's worth a <highlight>go</highlight>, isn't it?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它值得尝试一下，不是吗？

examination_example.sentence: She <highlight>went</highlight> camping.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她去露营了。

word_usage.usage: go是瞬间动词，不能和表示一段时间的状语连用。
go to后常接不带冠词的名词，表示进行一种活动，而非去什么地方。例如：go to school（上学）。
go用作不及物动词时，常可接带to的动词不定式，构成一个动词短语，表示“去做某事”。
go on表示“继续”时，其后可接动名词，不可直接接名词或代词，应该说go on with sth.，也不可接动词不定式。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 指按某一既定目标前进，取得发展，目的性很明确，强调经常和稳定地前进。
最常用词，含义宽泛而不确切，依上文确定其具体意思。
离开某地，侧重出发地而不是目的地。
最普通用词，指离开目前所在或所住之地，着重目的地而非出发地。
可与leave换用，强调目的地，但不及leave使用普遍。
最普通用词，作为连系动词，指从一个状态向另一个状态的变化。
常指某人或某物有意无意地获得引起变化的因素，从而变成另一状态。
常指逐渐地变成新状态，强调渐变的过程。
侧重指变得与原来截然不同，有时含贬义。
作为连系动词，通常与形容词连用，指进入某种状态，从而发生变化，多指不好的状态。
侧重变化的经过或过程，多用于不良情况。
